(5, 1, '2014-04-07 10:51:44', '2014-04-07 10:51:44', 'Acorn Agri (Pty) Ltd was incorporated in February 2014. The company serves as an investment holding company through which strategic agricultural investments can be made. Acorn Agri is managed by Acorn Private Equity, a specialist private equity fund manager.\r\n\r\nThe purpose of this vehicle is to capitalise on the consolidation of agri and food businesses that is currently taking place in Southern Africa. Significant corporate actions are underway and the opportunity exists to create a strong, diversified portfolio of businesses that will improve food security and increase sustainability of earnings.\r\n\r\nCurrently 40% of food is still imported into Sub-Saharan Africa, yet 60% of the world’s uncultivated arable land is in this region. There is a tremendous opportunity for growth in the agri space and Acorn Agri is positioning itself to be apart of this.\r\n\r\nThe investment philosophy is to search for excellent businesses with high quality management that can be acquired at reasonable prices. This will be done across various geographies and commodities thereby creating a diversified portfolio of assets. The businesses will then be strategically reorganised to create “pillars of excellence” across the various commodities and industries. These “pillars of excellence” will facilitate growth, sustainability and lead to further acquisitions and consolidation.\r\n\r\nWe believe Acorn Agri has the potential to become a very powerful agricultural company in the near future.', 'The Firm', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'about', '', '', '2014-05-06 14:50:29', '2014-05-06 12:50:29', '', 0, 'http://localhost/~tyronestafford/acorn/?page_id=5', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(6, 1, '2014-04-07 10:51:44', '2014-04-07 10:51:44', '', 'About Acorn', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '5-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-07 10:51:44', '2014-04-07 10:51:44', '', 5, 'http://localhost/~tyronestafford/acorn/?p=6', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(7, 1, '2014-04-07 10:51:54', '2014-04-07 10:51:54', 'Acorn is a specialist private equity fund manager and investment advisor focused exclusively on Sub-Saharan Africa.\r\n\r\nFounded in 2009, Acorn is a dedicated partner to all its investee companies, fostering sustainable businesses and generating long-term value for all stakeholders.\r\n\r\nThe Acorn investment team is committed to exceptional performance, uncompromising integrity, honesty and ethical business practices. These principles allow them to encourage value creation and support growth as opposed to maximising returns to the detriment of their underlying portfolio companies.\r\n\r\nThe Acorn principals have extensive experience in the agri sector and have been advisors to agri and food deals in excess of R1.6 billion.\r\n\r\n<strong>//LINK BUTTON: Acorn Website</strong>', 'APEQ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'apeq', '', '', '2014-05-09 12:18:29', '2014-05-09 10:18:29', '', 0, 'http://localhost/~tyronestafford/acorn/?page_id=7', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(8, 1, '2014-04-07 10:51:54', '2014-04-07 10:51:54', '', 'Business', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '7-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-07 10:51:54', '2014-04-07 10:51:54', '', 7, 'http://localhost/~tyronestafford/acorn/?p=8', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(9, 1, '2014-04-07 10:52:03', '2014-04-07 10:52:03', '<strong>OVERBERG AGRI</strong>\r\nPercentage Holding: 23%\r\n\r\nOverberg Agri is a regional agri services company based in Caledon in the Western Cape. It is a large provider of grain-, financial-, mechanisation- and irrigation services to farmers. It also has a number of retail stores, an abattoir and a lime mining business.\r\n\r\nOverberg Agri has strong, experienced management with the proven ability to unlock value. It has a regional monopoly in grain, good infrastructure and steady recurring income. It is also cash generative.\r\n\r\nThe shares in Overberg Agri were acquired at an attractive discount to NAV.', 'Investments', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'investments', '', '', '2014-05-06 14:49:49', '2014-05-06 12:49:49', '', 0, 'http://localhost/~tyronestafford/acorn/?page_id=9', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(10, 1, '2014-04-07 10:52:03', '2014-04-07 10:52:03', '', 'Investments', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '9-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-07 10:52:03', '2014-04-07 10:52:03', '', 9, 'http://localhost/~tyronestafford/acorn/?p=10', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(11, 1, '2014-04-07 10:52:40', '2014-04-07 10:52:40', 'At the core of the Acorn Equity investment ethos is a commitment to delivering returns to our investors and contributing to the generation of long-term sustainable value for other stakeholders through the adoption of responsible investment practises focused on environmental, social and governance issues. Integral to the investment decision-making and portfolio management processes, and to the best of their ability, the Acorn Equity team is specifically committed to:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Human rights</strong>\r\nRespect the protection of international human rights and avoid complicity in human rights violations.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Labour development and rights</strong>\r\nPromote sound labour development and rights practices, including considering employee working conditions, supporting the abolishment of child labour, promoting employees’ right to collective bargaining, eliminating forced labour, avoidance of employment discrimination and compliance with applicable labour laws.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>The environment</strong>\r\nTake a cautious and responsible approach to the environment, aiming to promote an appropriate level of environmental awareness and sound environmental practices in portfolio companies, including compliance with current environmental laws.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Anti-corruption</strong>\r\nAvoidance of corruption in all its forms and to subscribe to ethical behaviour that is captured in our membership to Unashamedly Ethical.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Robust corporate governance</strong>\r\nSeek to use governance structures that provide appropriate levels of oversight in the areas of audit, risk management and potential conflicts of interest and to implement compensation and other policies that align the interests of owners and management.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThese principles will be applied at all our investee companies, including Acorn Agri as well as all the companies in which Acorn Agri has a stake.\r\n\r\nAcorn Private Equity will provide timely information and maintain an open and transparent dialogue with investors on the matters addressed herein.', 'ESG', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'esg', '', '', '2014-05-06 17:23:59', '2014-05-06 15:23:59', '', 0, 'http://localhost/~tyronestafford/acorn/?page_id=11', 0, 'page', '', 0),
