(196, 1, '2014-04-24 14:50:56', '2014-04-24 12:50:56', 'Acorn Agri has a board of directors with a combined experience of over 100 years in agri and food businesses.\r\n<table style="width: 600px;">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><b>Name</b></td>\r\n<td><b>Role</b></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Cobus Visser</td>\r\n<td>Chairman</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Pierre Malan</td>\r\n<td>Executive Director</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Carl Neethling</td>\r\n<td>Executive Director</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Undisclosed Industry Expert</td>\r\n<td>Non-executive Director</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Undisclosed Industry Expert</td>\r\n<td>Non-executive Director</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'Directors', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '40-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-24 14:50:56', '2014-04-24 12:50:56', '', 40, 'http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/acorn_agri/htdocs/40-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(197, 1, '2014-04-24 14:54:42', '2014-04-24 12:54:42', 'The Acorn Agri concept has been well received by investors and the immediate funding target of R300m was quickly reached.  The next short-term target is to reach R500 million and the 18 – 36 month target is R1.5 billion.\r\n<table style="width: 600px;">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><b>Investor</b></td>\r\n<td><b>Percentage Holding</b></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Institutional Investor A</td>\r\n<td>33%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Institutional Investor B</td>\r\n<td>30%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Family Offices and Individuals</td>\r\n<td>30%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Acorn Private Equity</td>\r\n<td>7%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nNew investors are being sought and the minimum investment is R5 million.', 'Investors', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '42-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-24 14:54:42', '2014-04-24 12:54:42', '', 42, 'http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/acorn_agri/htdocs/42-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(198, 1, '2014-04-24 14:56:07', '2014-04-24 12:56:07', 'Acorn is a specialist private equity fund manager and investment advisor focussed exclusively on Sub-Saharan Africa.\n\nFounded in 2009, Acorn is a dedicated partner to all its investee companies, fostering sustainable businesses and generating long-term value for all stakeholders.\n\nThe Acorn investment team is committed to exceptional performance, uncompromising integrity, honesty and ethical business practices. These principles allow them to encourage value creation and support growth as opposed to maximising returns to the detriment of their underlying portfolio companies.\n\nThe Acorn principals have extensive experience in the agri sector and have been advisors to agri and food deals in excess of R1.6 billion.\n\nAcorn Website Link in the form of a botton&gt;&gt;', 'APEQ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '7-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-04-24 14:56:07', '2014-04-24 12:56:07', '', 7, 'http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/acorn_agri/htdocs/7-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
